  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Typically, it involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legitimate and re-entering it into the economy\n\nLegal definitions often include specific criminal activities like:\n- Hiding the origins of money from illegal sources\n- Conducting financial transactions to disguise illegal proceeds\n- Attempting to make criminally-derived funds look legitimate\n\nSpecific laws like the Bank Secrecy Act and anti-money laundering regulations provide detailed legal frameworks for identifying and prosecuting such activities.",
